    80	
    81	**Canonical orchestration**:
    82	
    83	> **Option B+ — Process-distributed, Tape-continuous runtime**.
    84	> 每个 problem 可以由 subprocess 执行；但所有 subprocess 必须 resume 同一条
    85	> ChainTape：same runtime_repo / same CAS / same agent registry / same system
    86	> pubkeys / same batch_id / continuous HEAD_t / no fresh genesis / no
    87	> memory-only cross-task state.
    88	
    89	**Disposition**:
    90	- Option A (single-process loop) → dev-only harness; not ship evidence.
    91	- Option B (subprocess + resume) → canonical (with B+ hardening below).
    92	- Option C (hybrid) → allowed only as wrapper over Option B+ semantics.
    93	
    94	**Binding principle (architect §7)**:
    95	
    96	> **进程是否重启不重要，tape 是否连续才重要。**
    97	> 图灵机可以停机再启动，但纸带不能换。
    98	
    99	**SG-G1.7 reworded** (replaces any "one process" language):
   100	
   101	> A batch of >=3 tasks must execute on **one continuous ChainTape**:
   102	> same runtime_repo / same CAS / exactly one genesis /
   103	> `task_{k+1}.start_head_t == task_k.end_head_t` / agent balances /
   104	> positions / reputation persist across task boundaries.
   105	
   106	**Resume contract** (not just env var; explicit fail-closed args):
   107	- `--runtime-repo`
   108	- `--cas`
   109	- `--expected-head-t`
   110	- `--batch-id`
   111	- `--task-id`
   112	- `--agent-registry`
